{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"1da8499d-c2ca-4222-8d7d-40d4f6e5df37","content":"**Starting with MSTest.Sdk 4.0.0, the VSTest compatibility layer is no longer included by default.** The SDK now exclusively targets Microsoft.Testing.Platform as the runner.\n\nThis means `vstest.console.exe` (and `dotnet test` in VSTest mode) can no longer discover or run your tests — there's no VSTest adapter in the output.\n\n### Fix options\n\n1. **Re-enable VSTest support** by adding this to your `.csproj`:\n\n   ```xml\n   <EnableMicrosoftTestingExtensionsCodeCoverage>true</EnableMicrosoftTestingExtensionsCodeCoverage>\n   ```\n   or more directly:\n   ```xml\n   <EnableMSTestRunner>true</EnableMSTestRunner>\n   <TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport>true</TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport>\n   ```\n\n2. **Migrate your CI pipeline** to use `dotnet test` (which in .NET 9+ uses Microsoft.Testing.Platform natively) or run the test executable directly:\n\n   ```bash\n   dotnet test --no-build\n   # or\n   ./TestProject --report-trx\n   ```\n\nOption 2 is the recommended path forward — VSTest is being phased out in favor of Microsoft.Testing.Platform.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"5e600cdb-bd69-4a9b-839c-f36b51f22074","outputTokens":311,"requestId":"4811:E3CA7:614BA76:69D3BDD:69FC01FC"},"id":"f71ba689-7944-483e-baf7-443b1229c4c2","timestamp":"2026-05-07T03:07:49.584Z","parentId":"bd0c2f49-63b2-4e2a-afe4-9bbc8ad0e5b0"}
